\section{Task, Data, and Models}
\label{Task}

\subsection{Task Definition}

We study \emph{cross-lingual clinical conversation summarization}: given a
multi-turn doctor-patient conversation in one of ten Indian languages, generate a structured English clinical summary. The target summary is always in English, matching realistic deployment contexts where medical records are maintained in English while consultations occur in the patient's native language.

\subsection{Dataset}

We use the dataset from the Shared Task on Patient-Centric Clinical
Dialogue Summarization\footnote{\url{https://www.codabench.org/competitions/10527/}},
which provides multilingual doctor-patient dialogues paired with English clinical summaries. Dialogues exhibit features typical of clinical discourse: domain-specific terminology, code-switching between English and regional languages, and the asymmetric turn-taking patterns of medical consultations. Table~\ref{tab:language_data} describes the language properties.

