\textit{Clinical entity analysis}: GPT-4.1 extracts five entity categories; Symptoms, Diagnoses, Substances and Habits, Procedures
and Tests, Treatments from both generated and doctor-patient conversation, normalizing morphological variants to canonical forms. A generated entity is a true positive (TP) if semantically equivalent to a gold
entity; a false positive (FP, or \textit{hallucination}) if it
appears in the generated but not the conversation; a false negative
(FN, or \textit{omission}) if a gold entity is absent from the
generated summary. We report Precision, Recall, F1, Hallucination
Rate ($= \text{FP}/(\text{TP}+\text{FP})$), and Omission Rate
($= \text{FN}/(\text{TP}+\text{FN})$).





